‚úÖ LAN Troubleshooting ‚Äì Brief Summary
‚¶Å	Check LAN cable, port lights, and switch/router connection.
‚¶Å	Ensure Ethernet adapter is enabled.
‚¶Å	Verify IP using ipconfig (check gateway & DNS).
‚¶Å	Ping gateway and server to test connectivity.
‚¶Å	Update or reinstall LAN driver.
‚¶Å	Disable/enable the adapter or change cable/port.

‚úÖ Wi-Fi Troubleshooting ‚Äì Brief Summary
‚¶Å	Ensure Wi-Fi is ON and airplane mode is OFF.
‚¶Å	Forget and reconnect to Wi-Fi network.
‚¶Å	Restart router and check if other devices connect.
‚¶Å	Check IP address and renew IP.
‚¶Å	Improve signal strength (move closer to router).
‚¶Å	Update/reinstall Wi-Fi driver.
‚¶Å	Reset network settings if needed.


üì∂ Difference Between 2.4 GHz and 5 GHz Wi-Fi Bands
Feature	2.4 GHz (2.5G)	5 GHz
Speed	Slower (up to 450 Mbps) 	Faster (up to 1300 Mbps or more)
Range	Longer range ‚Äì covers more area 	Shorter range ‚Äì covers smaller area
Interference	More interference (shared with Bluetooth, microwaves, etc.)	Less interference ‚Äì cleaner signal
